{
  "page": "Ellaria Sand",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\">Ellaria Sand</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Ellaria_Sand.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Ellaria Sand.jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/8/85/Ellaria_Sand.jpg/350px-Ellaria_Sand.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"538\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/8/85/Ellaria_Sand.jpg/525px-Ellaria_Sand.jpg 1.5x, /images/8/85/Ellaria_Sand.jpg 2x\" /></a><div>Ellaria Sand, by Amok ©</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Alias</th><td>\nThe serpent's whore<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiances</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Uller\" title=\"House Uller\">House Uller</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Martell\" title=\"House Martell\">House Martell</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Dornishmen\" title=\"Dornishmen\">Dornishmen</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dorne</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafellaria_sand.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafellaria_sand.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Father</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Harmen_Uller\" title=\"Harmen Uller\">Harmen Uller</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Lover</th><td>\nPrince <a href=\"/index.php/Oberyn_Martell\" title=\"Oberyn Martell\">Oberyn Martell</a> (<a href=\"/index.php/Paramour\" title=\"Paramour\">paramour</a>)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Issue</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Elia_Sand\" title=\"Elia Sand\">Elia Sand</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Obella_Sand\" title=\"Obella Sand\">Obella Sand</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Dorea_Sand\" title=\"Dorea Sand\">Dorea Sand</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Loreza_Sand\" title=\"Loreza Sand\">Loreza Sand</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i> (appears)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i> (appears)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Winds_of_Winter\" title=\"The Winds of Winter\">The Winds of Winter</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><span style=\"white-space:nowrap\">Played by</span></th><td>\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indira_Varma\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Indira Varma\">Indira Varma</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><span style=\"white-space:nowrap\">TV series</span></th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"Game of Thrones\">Game of Thrones</a></i>: <br /><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones_-_Season_4\" title=\"Game of Thrones - Season 4\">Season 4</a> | <a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones_-_Season_5\" title=\"Game of Thrones - Season 5\">5</a> | <a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones_-_Season_6\" title=\"Game of Thrones - Season 6\">6</a> | <a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones_-_Season_7\" title=\"Game of Thrones - Season 7\">7</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Ellaria Sand</b> is the beloved <a href=\"/index.php/Paramour\" title=\"Paramour\">paramour</a> of Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Oberyn_Martell\" title=\"Oberyn Martell\">Oberyn Martell</a>, and the mother of the four youngest \"<a href=\"/index.php/Sand_Snakes\" title=\"Sand Snakes\">Sand Snakes</a>,\" Oberyn's <a href=\"/index.php/Bastard\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bastard\">bastard</a> daughters. Ellaria herself is the bastard daughter of <a href=\"/index.php/Harmen_Uller\" title=\"Harmen Uller\">Harmen Uller</a>, Lord of <a href=\"/index.php/Hellholt\" title=\"Hellholt\">Hellholt</a>.\n</p><p>In the television adaptation <i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"Game of Thrones\">Game of Thrones</a></i>, Ellaria is portrayed by <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indira_Varma\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Indira Varma\">Indira Varma</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance_and_Character\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance and Character</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#The_Winds_of_Winter\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>The Winds of Winter</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Quotes_by_Ellaria\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes by Ellaria</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#Quotes_about_Ellaria\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes about Ellaria</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#Family\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Family</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-11\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance_and_Character\">Appearance and Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ellaria_Sand&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance and Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">See also: <a href=\"/index.php/Category:Images_of_Ellaria_Sand\" title=\"Category:Images of Ellaria Sand\">Images of Ellaria Sand</a></div>\n<p>Although not accounted as a beautiful woman, Ellaria is regarded as attractive and eye-catching, with an exotic, sensuous flair.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> She has black hair.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> She is described as a good woman, strong and brave, with a gentle heart.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> Ellaria is believed to worship a <a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lysene</a> love goddess.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> She is described by her paramour, <a href=\"/index.php/Oberyn_Martell\" title=\"Oberyn Martell\">Oberyn Martell</a>, as being sexually adventurous and potentially bisexual.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Olenna_Tyrell\" title=\"Olenna Tyrell\">Olenna Tyrell</a>, who is angry at Oberyn for having crippled her grandson <a href=\"/index.php/Willas_Tyrell\" title=\"Willas Tyrell\">Willas Tyrell</a> in a <a href=\"/index.php/Tourney\" title=\"Tourney\">tourney</a> accident, disparages Ellaria as \"the <a href=\"/index.php/Serpent\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Serpent\">serpent</a>'s <a href=\"/index.php/Whore\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Whore\">whore</a>\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ellaria_Sand&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ellaria_Sand&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>When Oberyn Martell travels to <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> to take the seat on the <a href=\"/index.php/Small_council\" title=\"Small council\">small council</a> offered to his brother <a href=\"/index.php/Doran_Martell\" title=\"Doran Martell\">Doran Martell</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Prince_of_Dorne\" title=\"Prince of Dorne\">Prince of Dorne</a>, Ellaria accompanies him.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Oberyn hints to <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a> that Ellaria wants to sleep with Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos66.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos66.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>She is a guest at the <a href=\"/index.php/Purple_Wedding\" title=\"Purple Wedding\">royal wedding</a> of King <a href=\"/index.php/Joffrey_Baratheon\" title=\"Joffrey Baratheon\">Joffrey I Baratheon</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Margaery_Tyrell\" title=\"Margaery Tyrell\">Margaery Tyrell</a>, seated with other <a href=\"/index.php/Dornishmen\" title=\"Dornishmen\">Dornishmen</a> at a place of honor, but away from the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Tyrell\" title=\"House Tyrell\">Tyrells</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos60.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos60.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>Ellaria is also present at the <a href=\"/index.php/Trial_by_combat\" title=\"Trial by combat\">trial by combat</a> for Tyrion Lannister, where Oberyn serves as his champion, and she witnesses Oberyn's death at the hands of Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Gregor_Clegane\" title=\"Gregor Clegane\">Gregor Clegane</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos70.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos70.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ellaria_Sand&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Ellaria_Sand_by_elalendi.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/0/0d/Ellaria_Sand_by_elalendi.png/350px-Ellaria_Sand_by_elalendi.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"504\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/0/0d/Ellaria_Sand_by_elalendi.png 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Ellaria_Sand_by_elalendi.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Ellaria Sand, <a href=\"/index.php/Oberyn_Martell\" title=\"Oberyn Martell\">the Red Viper's</a> widow, by elalendi ©</div></div></div>\n<p>After Oberyn's death, Ellaria escorts his remains back to <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dorne</a>. After Prince Doran arrests the eldest <a href=\"/index.php/Sand_Snakes\" title=\"Sand Snakes\">Sand Snakes</a>, Ellaria and her daughters are secluded in the <a href=\"/index.php/Water_Gardens\" title=\"Water Gardens\">Water Gardens</a>, to prevent them from being used in the plots of others.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc40.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc40.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ellaria_Sand&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Ellaria is present at the feast in honor of Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Balon_Swann\" title=\"Balon Swann\">Balon Swann</a>'s arrival at <a href=\"/index.php/Sunspear\" title=\"Sunspear\">Sunspear</a>, where he delivers the skull of Gregor Clegane to Prince Doran.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>Ellaria is later summoned to Doran's private chambers for a conference between him, his daughter <a href=\"/index.php/Arianne_Martell\" title=\"Arianne Martell\">Arianne Martell</a>, and the eldest Sand Snakes. She becomes distraught when she hears <a href=\"/index.php/Obara_Sand\" title=\"Obara Sand\">Obara Sand</a>'s statement that Gregor's death \"is a start\". With <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin Lannister</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_Baratheon\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Robert Baratheon\">Robert Baratheon</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Amory_Lorch\" title=\"Amory Lorch\">Amory Lorch</a> and now the Mountain dead, everyone who was part of the death of <a href=\"/index.php/Elia_Martell\" title=\"Elia Martell\">Elia Martell</a> and her children, Ellaria wants it to be an end. Ellaria fears for her own daughters, who admire Obara, <a href=\"/index.php/Nymeria_Sand\" title=\"Nymeria Sand\">Nymeria</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Tyene_Sand\" title=\"Tyene Sand\">Tyene Sand</a>, and fears where the quest for revenge will lead them. Doran comforts Ellaria, and tells her to go to her girls while promising no harm will come to them, and then continues the conference without her.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"The_Winds_of_Winter\"><i>The Winds of Winter</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ellaria_Sand&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: The Winds of Winter\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<table style=\"margin: 4px 10%; border: 1px solid #aaa; background:#fbfbfb;\"><tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"padding: 2px 0 2px 0.5em;border-left: 10px solid #f28500;\">\n<div style=\"width: 50px;\"><img alt=\"Content.png\" src=\"/images/c/cc/Content.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" />\n</div></td><td style=\"border: none; padding: 0.25em 0.9em; width: 100%;\"> <b>Warning</b> <br /> This information has thus far been released in a sample chapter for <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Winds_of_Winter\" title=\"The Winds of Winter\">The Winds of Winter</a></i>, and might therefore not be in finalized form. Keep in mind that the content as described below is still subject to change.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>Doran sends Ellaria to her father <a href=\"/index.php/Harmen_Uller\" title=\"Harmen Uller\">Harmen Uller</a>'s seat at <a href=\"/index.php/Hellholt\" title=\"Hellholt\">Hellholt</a>, along with her youngest daughter, <a href=\"/index.php/Loreza_Sand\" title=\"Loreza Sand\">Loreza Sand</a>. Ellaria's daughter <a href=\"/index.php/Elia_Sand\" title=\"Elia Sand\">Elia</a> is one of Arianne's traveling companions, <a href=\"/index.php/Obella_Sand\" title=\"Obella Sand\">Obella</a> is sent to <a href=\"/index.php/Sunspear\" title=\"Sunspear\">Sunspear</a> to serve as a <a href=\"/index.php/Cupbearer\" title=\"Cupbearer\">cupbearer</a> to the wife of its <a href=\"/index.php/Castellan\" title=\"Castellan\">castellan</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Manfrey_Martell\" title=\"Manfrey Martell\">Manfrey Martell</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Dorea_Sand\" title=\"Dorea Sand\">Dorea</a> remains at the <a href=\"/index.php/Water_Gardens\" title=\"Water Gardens\">Water Gardens</a> with Doran.<sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes_by_Ellaria\">Quotes by Ellaria</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ellaria_Sand&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes by Ellaria\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Oberyn_Martell\" title=\"Oberyn Martell\">Oberyn</a> wanted vengeance for <a href=\"/index.php/Elia_Martell\" title=\"Elia Martell\">Elia</a>. Now the three of you want vengeance for him. I have four daughters, I remind you. <a href=\"/index.php/Sand_Snakes\" title=\"Sand Snakes\">Your sisters</a>. My <a href=\"/index.php/Elia_Sand\" title=\"Elia Sand\">Elia</a> is fourteen, almost a woman. <a href=\"/index.php/Obella_Sand\" title=\"Obella Sand\">Obella</a> is twelve, on the brink of maidenhood. They worship you, as <a href=\"/index.php/Dorea_Sand\" title=\"Dorea Sand\">Dorea</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Loreza_Sand\" title=\"Loreza Sand\">Loreza</a> worship them. If you should die, must El and Obella seek vengeance for you, then Dorea and Loree for them? Is that how it goes, round and round forever? I ask again, <b>where does it end?</b> I saw your father die. Here is <a href=\"/index.php/Gregor_Clegane\" title=\"Gregor Clegane\">his killer</a>. Can I take a skull to bed with me, to give me comfort in the night? Will it make me laugh, write me songs, care for me when I am old and sick?<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;Ellaria to <a href=\"/index.php/Obara_Sand\" title=\"Obara Sand\">Obara</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Nymeria_Sand\" title=\"Nymeria Sand\">Nymeria</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Tyene_Sand\" title=\"Tyene Sand\">Tyene Sand</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes_about_Ellaria\">Quotes about Ellaria</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ellaria_Sand&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes about Ellaria\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:322px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Ellaria_Sand.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/3/3d/Ellaria_Sand.png\" width=\"320\" height=\"480\" class=\"thumbimage\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Ellaria_Sand.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indira_Varma\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Indira Varma\">Indira Varma</a> as Ellaria in <i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"Game of Thrones\">Game of Thrones</a></i></div></div></div>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Shae\" title=\"Shae\">Shae</a> had told her that this Ellaria worshiped some <a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lysene</a> love goddess. \"She was almost a <a href=\"/index.php/Whore\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Whore\">whore</a> when he found her, m'lady,\" her maid confided, \"and now she's near a princess.\" Sansa had never been this close to the <a href=\"/index.php/Dornishmen\" title=\"Dornishmen\">Dornishwoman</a> before. She is not truly beautiful, she thought, but something about her draws the eye.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Sansa_Stark\" title=\"Sansa Stark\">Sansa Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Even weeping, she has a strength in her.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Areo_Hotah\" title=\"Areo Hotah\">Areo Hotah</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Nymeria</b>: I know she loved <a href=\"/index.php/Oberyn_Martell\" title=\"Oberyn Martell\">our father</a> well, but it is plain she never understood him.<br />\n<b>Doran</b>: She understood more than you ever will, Nymeria. And she made your father happy. In the end a gentle heart may be worth more than pride or valor. Be that as it may, there are things Ellaria does not know and should not know. This war has already begun.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Nymeria_Sand\" title=\"Nymeria Sand\">Nymeria Sand</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Doran_Martell\" title=\"Doran Martell\">Doran Martell</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family\">Family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ellaria_Sand&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Family\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div style=\"overflow:auto;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:separate;font: 90% sans-serif;\">\t\n<tbody><tr align=\"center\"><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td><div style=\"width:1em; height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:1em; height:1em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#16